C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_8_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20also%20destroyed%20the%20forces%20of%20Hadadezer%20son%20of%20Rehob%2C%20king%20of%20Zobah%2C%20when%20Hadadezer%20marched%20out%20to%20strengthen%20his%20control%20along%20the%20Euphrates%20River.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_8_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20captured%201%2C000%20chariots%2C%207%2C000%20charioteers%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E8%3A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Dead%20Sea%20Scrolls%20and%20Greek%20version%20(see%20also%201%26%23xA0%3BChr%2018%3A4)%3B%20Masoretic%20Text%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ecaptured%201%2C700%20charioteers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%2020%2C000%20foot%20soldiers.%20He%20crippled%20all%20the%20chariot%20horses%20except%20enough%20for%20100%26%23xA0%3Bchariots.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_8_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Arameans%20from%20Damascus%20arrived%20to%20help%20King%20Hadadezer%2C%20David%20killed%2022%2C000%20of%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_8_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20placed%20several%20army%20garrisons%20in%20Damascus%2C%20the%20Aramean%20capital%2C%20and%20the%20Arameans%20became%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20subjects%20and%20paid%20him%20tribute%20money.%20So%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20made%20David%20victorious%20wherever%20he%20went.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_8_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%228%22%20vn%3D%227%2